info.headline: Coastal Flood Warning issued November 6 at 2:03PM PST until November 6 at 10:00PM PST by NWS Seattle WA
info.description:
* WHAT...For the High Surf Advisory, large breaking waves. For the Coastal Flood Warning, significant moderate to major coastal flooding. Inundation of two to three feet above ground level is possible along shorelines and low lying coastal areas. For the Coastal Flood Advisory, minor coastal flooding expected. Inundation of up to two feet above ground level is possible along shorelines and low-lying coastal areas.
* WHERE...Grays Harbor County Coast zone, including Westport.
* WHEN...For the High Surf Advisory, until 7 AM PST Friday. For the Coastal Flood Warning, until 10 PM PST this evening. For the Coastal Flood Advisory, from 10 AM to 3 PM PST Friday.
* IMPACTS...Significant coastal flooding due to high tides and storm surge is expected. This is expected to lead to numerous road closures. Low lying property including homes, businesses, and some critical infrastructure may be inundated. Shoreline erosion or damage may occur. Strong surf can knock people off their feet, move driftwood and debris causing injury, and cause localized beach and coastal erosion.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...High surf will continue tonight, before waves begin to gradually subside during the day Friday. Warning level coastal flooding will decrease this afternoon, but one final day of minor coastal flooding is expected around high tide on Friday.
info.instruction:
Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone property. If travel is required, do not drive around barricades or through water of unknown depth.
Inundation above ground level refers to the height above the Mean Higher High Water (MHHW) level.
Never turn your back on the ocean and keep children and pets close. Know the tides and surf forecast. Follow warning signs and respect barriers.
